ğŸ’¡ Code Implementation
1ï¸âƒ£ Restaurant.java (Base Class)

Path: com/swiggy/base/Restaurant.java

package com.swiggy.base;

public class Restaurant {
    protected String name;
    protected String location;

    public Restaurant(String name, String location) {
        this.name = name;
        this.location = location;
    }

    public void displayDetails() {
        System.out.println("Restaurant Name: " + name);
        System.out.println("Location: " + location);
    }

    public void prepareFood() {
        System.out.println("Restaurant is preparing food...");
    }
}

2ï¸âƒ£ Order.java (Parent Class for Orders)

Path: com/swiggy/orders/Order.java

package com.swiggy.orders;

import com.swiggy.base.Restaurant;

public class Order extends Restaurant {
    protected String customerName;
    protected double price;

    public Order(String restaurantName, String location, String customerName, double price) {
        super(restaurantName, location);
        this.customerName = customerName;
        this.price = price;
    }

    public void orderDetails() {
        System.out.println("Customer: " + customerName);
        System.out.println("Total Price: â‚¹" + price);
    }

    public void deliver() {
        System.out.println("Delivering your order soon...");
    }
}

3ï¸âƒ£ VegOrder.java (Child Class)

Path: com/swiggy/orders/VegOrder.java

package com.swiggy.orders;

public class VegOrder extends Order {

    public VegOrder(String restaurantName, String location, String customerName, double price) {
        super(restaurantName, location, customerName, price);
    }

    // Method Overriding
    @Override
    public void deliver() {
        System.out.println("Delivering fresh and healthy Veg meal ğŸ± to " + customerName);
    }
}

4ï¸âƒ£ NonVegOrder.java (Child Class)

Path: com/swiggy/orders/NonVegOrder.java

package com.swiggy.orders;

public class NonVegOrder extends Order {

    public NonVegOrder(String restaurantName, String location, String customerName, double price) {
        super(restaurantName, location, customerName, price);
    }

    // Method Overriding
    @Override
    public void deliver() {
        System.out.println("Delivering hot and spicy Non-Veg meal ğŸ— to " + customerName);
    }
}

5ï¸âƒ£ SwiggyApp.java (Main Class)

Path: com/swiggy/main/SwiggyApp.java

package com.swiggy.main;

import com.swiggy.orders.VegOrder;
import com.swiggy.orders.NonVegOrder;

public class SwiggyApp {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        System.out.println("===== Welcome to Swiggy Food Delivery System ğŸ• =====");

        VegOrder veg = new VegOrder("GreenBite", "Hyderabad", "Ananya", 250.0);
        NonVegOrder nonveg = new NonVegOrder("SpiceHub", "Bangalore", "Ravi", 400.0);

        System.out.println("\n--- Veg Order Details ---");
        veg.displayDetails();
        veg.orderDetails();
        veg.deliver(); // Overridden method

        System.out.println("\n--- Non-Veg Order Details ---");
        nonveg.displayDetails();
        nonveg.orderDetails();
        nonveg.deliver(); // Overridden method

        System.out.println("\n===== Thank You for using Swiggy! âœ¨ =====");
    }
}

ğŸ¯ Key Concepts Demonstrated
Concept	Description	Example
Inheritance	Order inherits from Restaurant, VegOrder and NonVegOrder inherit from Order	class VegOrder extends Order
Method Overriding	Child classes redefine deliver() method	VegOrder.deliver() vs NonVegOrder.deliver()
Packages	Classes are organized by functionality	com.swiggy.base, com.swiggy.orders, com.swiggy.main
